    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.24a-24b_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">24a</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>4/20/58</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Words cannot express our sorrow when we learned of Mrs. Neihardt's death. The full impact of it has not yet soaked in as we are still in a state of shock from my step-father's death. She was the dearest, sweetest woman and we loved her like a grandmother. Our love for her, of course, was not as deep as yours. Even though she was better prepared for the next world than most, her presence here will be sorely missed by all who loved and knew her. Your life together was a classic story of love and devotion. Willa and I have tried to pattern our married life after yours since we first met you. While we may not be as successful as you. We do feel our married life is much more successful than most of our friends. We are more in love now than when we got married are growing more in love each day we live. A good deal of this we attribute to <add>the</add> example you and Mrs. Neihardt set for us.</p>
                
                <p>If you feel as though you would like a change of scenery &#8212; please remember that we always have an extra bed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Our deepest love,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Jack + Willa</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
